WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.033 --> 00:00:06.534
♪♪

00:00:06.534 --> 00:00:08.901
Narrator:
NO ONE KNOWS WHO CAME UP WITH
THE IDEA OF SQUEEZING ORANGES

00:00:08.901 --> 00:00:10.267
TO MAKE JUICE.

00:00:10.267 --> 00:00:13.234
THE POPULARITY OF ORANGE JUICE
INCREASED DRAMATICALLY

00:00:13.234 --> 00:00:15.300
IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE 20th CENTURY

00:00:15.300 --> 00:00:18.734
AS TECHNIQUES WERE DEVELOPED
TO EXTEND ITS SHELF LIFE.

00:00:18.734 --> 00:00:22.968
TODAY, MANY PEOPLE START THEIR
DAY WITH A TALL GLASS OF OJ.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.834
IN ITS PUREST FORM,
ORANGE JUICE IS FRESH-SQUEEZED

00:00:28.834 --> 00:00:32.334
AND MADE WITH NO PRESERVATIVES
OR OTHER ADDITIVES.

00:00:32.334 --> 00:00:34.767
THE APPEAL IS INDISPUTABLE.

00:00:34.767 --> 00:00:37.834
FRESH-SQUEEZED OJ
CONTAINS VITAMIN C,

00:00:37.834 --> 00:00:41.000
AND THE FLAVOR IS AUTHENTIC.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:44.267
ORANGE JUICE PRODUCTION
STARTS IN GROVES.

00:00:44.267 --> 00:00:46.701
THE TREES TAKE SEVERAL MONTHS
TO BEAR FRUIT,

00:00:46.701 --> 00:00:49.267
AND ARE HARVESTED
IN EARLY NOVEMBER.

00:00:49.267 --> 00:00:51.400
♪♪

00:00:51.400 --> 00:00:55.067
PICKING ORANGES IS A JOB
THAT'S DONE ENTIRELY BY HAND.

00:00:55.067 --> 00:00:57.367
AN AUTOMATED PICKING SYSTEM
COULD DAMAGE

00:00:57.367 --> 00:01:01.100
BOTH THE TREES AND THE FRUIT.

00:01:01.100 --> 00:01:04.000
THE PICKER USES A BAG MADE
OF VINYL COMPOSITE

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:07.100
THAT'S LIGHTWEIGHT
AND HEAVY-DUTY.

00:01:07.100 --> 00:01:10.067
THERE ARE MULTIPLE TYPES OF
JUICING ORANGES.

00:01:10.067 --> 00:01:13.334
THIS ONE IS CALLED THE HAMLIN.

00:01:13.334 --> 00:01:15.667
HAMLIN ORANGES
ARE SMALL AND JUICY,

00:01:15.667 --> 00:01:17.767
THE TREES THEY GROW ON
ARE PRODUCTIVE

00:01:17.767 --> 00:01:19.734
AND RESILIENT TO COLD.

00:01:19.734 --> 00:01:22.267
THE PICKER PLUCKS THE FRUIT
FROM THE TREES

00:01:22.267 --> 00:01:24.334
BEFORE THEY TURN ORANGE.

00:01:24.334 --> 00:01:26.334
THEY MAY BE GREEN
ON THE OUTSIDE,

00:01:26.334 --> 00:01:29.133
BUT THEY ARE STILL SWEET
ON THE INSIDE.

00:01:29.133 --> 00:01:31.467
THE FRUITS'
SIZE AND CONDITION

00:01:31.467 --> 00:01:35.334
ARE INDICATIONS
OF MATURITY AND FLAVOR.

00:01:35.334 --> 00:01:37.434
AS THE PICKER EMPTIES THE BAG
INTO A BIN,

00:01:37.434 --> 00:01:40.968
HE EXAMINES THE ORANGES.

00:01:40.968 --> 00:01:42.767
ANYTHING WITH TEARS OR PUNCTURES

00:01:42.767 --> 00:01:45.334
MAY ALSO HAVE
INTERNAL DEGRADATION,

00:01:45.334 --> 00:01:50.033
BUT SUPERFICIAL FLAWS WON'T
AFFECT THE QUALITY OF THE JUICE.

00:01:50.033 --> 00:01:52.400
THE ORANGES ARE TAKEN TO A
PROCESSING FACILITY,

00:01:52.400 --> 00:01:55.300
AND TRANSFERRED
TO A SLOPED CHUTE.

00:01:55.300 --> 00:01:58.834
♪♪

00:01:58.834 --> 00:02:03.000
THE GRADIENT OF THE CHUTE
PREVENTS DAMAGE,

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:05.868
AS THE ORANGES TUMBLE
INTO A WASH STATION.

00:02:05.868 --> 00:02:09.601
♪♪

00:02:09.601 --> 00:02:12.868
A SPRAYER RAINS SOAPY WATER
ONTO THE ORANGES

00:02:12.868 --> 00:02:16.100
AS SPIRALING NYLON
BRUSHES SCRUB AND CLEAN

00:02:16.100 --> 00:02:18.534
WHILE SIMULTANEOUSLY
MOVING THEM FORWARD.

00:02:18.534 --> 00:02:21.100
♪♪

00:02:21.100 --> 00:02:24.767
AFTER THE WASH,
ANOTHER SPRAYER RINSES THEM OFF

00:02:24.767 --> 00:02:29.434
AS THE SPIRALING BRUSHES
CONTINUE SCRUBBING.

00:02:29.434 --> 00:02:32.434
THE ORANGES TRANSITION
TO A ROLLER CONVEYOR

00:02:32.434 --> 00:02:34.968
THAT TAKES THEM
UP AND UNDER FANS.

00:02:34.968 --> 00:02:39.534
♪♪

00:02:39.534 --> 00:02:43.634
AS THE ORANGES EXIT THE DRYER,
AN INSPECTOR CHECKS THEM

00:02:43.634 --> 00:02:45.534
FOR ANY MISSED DAMAGE.

00:02:45.534 --> 00:02:50.734
♪♪

00:02:50.734 --> 00:02:54.534
THE ORANGES TRAVEL ACROSS
MORE REVOLVING BRUSHES.

00:02:54.534 --> 00:02:56.501
THE BRISTLES ON THESE BRUSHES
ARE GENTLER

00:02:56.501 --> 00:02:58.234
THAN ON THE FIRST GROUP.

00:02:58.234 --> 00:03:01.834
THEY BUFF THE SKIN OF THE FRUIT
AND REMOVE ANY RESIDUAL DIRT.

00:03:01.834 --> 00:03:04.734
♪♪

00:03:04.734 --> 00:03:08.801
FINALLY, THE ORANGES
FALL OFF THE CONVEYOR LINE

00:03:08.801 --> 00:03:10.801
INTO A BIN.

00:03:10.801 --> 00:03:13.567
NOW CLEANED,
THE ORANGES CAN BE JUICED

00:03:13.567 --> 00:03:16.534
WITH NO CONTAMINANTS THAT COULD
SPOIL EITHER THE PRODUCT

00:03:16.534 --> 00:03:20.501
OR JUICING MACHINERY.

00:03:20.501 --> 00:03:22.067
AS A FINAL PRECAUTION,

00:03:22.067 --> 00:03:26.100
THE JUICING OPERATOR
PERFORMS ONE LAST INSPECTION.

00:03:26.100 --> 00:03:28.901
IF SHE'S COMPLETELY SATISFIED
WITH THEIR CLEANLINESS

00:03:28.901 --> 00:03:30.434
AND GENERAL CONDITION,

00:03:30.434 --> 00:03:32.934
SHE LOADS THE ORANGES
INTO THE EXTRACTOR.

00:03:32.934 --> 00:03:36.567
♪♪

00:03:36.567 --> 00:03:39.467
THERE'S NO NEED TO SLICE THEM
BEFOREHAND.

00:03:39.467 --> 00:03:42.167
SHE FEEDS THEM TO
THE JUICING MACHINE WHOLE.

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.400
THE SYSTEM FEEDS THE ORANGES
ONE AT A TIME TO THE EXTRACTOR.

00:03:48.400 --> 00:03:50.534
THE EXTRACTOR
PUNCTURES THE FRUIT,

00:03:50.534 --> 00:03:53.467
AND METAL TEETH PEEL
AWAY THE SKIN.

00:03:53.467 --> 00:03:55.300
IT SQUEEZES OUT THE JUICE

00:03:55.300 --> 00:03:58.133
WHILE SIMULTANEOUSLY
FILTERING OUT THE SEEDS,

00:03:58.133 --> 00:04:00.601
AND THE MEMBRANE BETWEEN
THE FLESH OF THE ORANGE

00:04:00.601 --> 00:04:03.601
AND THE SKIN.

00:04:03.601 --> 00:04:07.701
THE JUICE FLOWS INTO A VAT.

00:04:07.701 --> 00:04:08.934
A SCREEN IN THE VAT

00:04:08.934 --> 00:04:12.200
FILTERS THE PULP TO
THE DESIRED CONSISTENCY --

00:04:12.200 --> 00:04:13.667
THERE ARE SEVERAL
DIFFERENT FILTERS

00:04:13.667 --> 00:04:18.100
FOR DIFFERENT AMOUNTS
OF PULP.

00:04:18.100 --> 00:04:21.100
THE JUICE IS BOTTLED IN JUGS.

00:04:21.100 --> 00:04:23.868
THE PLASTIC JUGS WILL
ACCOMMODATE ANY EXPANSION

00:04:23.868 --> 00:04:33.300
OF THE UNPASTEURIZED JUICE
DUE TO FERMENTATION.

00:04:33.300 --> 00:04:36.334
INSTEAD OF PASTEURIZING THIS
FRESH-SQUEEZED JUICE,

00:04:36.334 --> 00:04:39.167
IT IS CHILLED IMMEDIATELY.

00:04:39.167 --> 00:04:40.934
THE UNPASTEURIZED ORANGE JUICE

00:04:40.934 --> 00:04:42.934
WON'T HAVE
AN EXTENDED SHELF LIFE,

00:04:42.934 --> 00:04:46.133
BUT THE TRADE-OFF IS
AN UNALTERED FLAVOR AND COLOR.

00:04:46.133 --> 00:04:50.367
♪♪

00:04:50.367 --> 00:04:53.234
REFRIGERATION WILL PRESERVE
THE JUICE FOR A FEW DAYS,

00:04:53.234 --> 00:04:56.367
AND AFTER ALL,
FRESH-SQUEEZED ORANGE JUICE

00:04:56.367 --> 00:04:58.968
IS A DRINK
THAT'S BEST SERVED COLD.

